*mx4j-3.0.1-r2 (07 Dec 2006)

  07 Dec 2006; Petteri Räty <betelgeuse@gentoo.org> metadata.xml,
  +mx4j-3.0.1-r2.ebuild:
  Beginning with this revision mx4j is a metapackage pulling in
  dev-java/mx4j-core and dev-java/mx4j-tools. This was done to reduce
  dependencies in packages that only require the core. See bug #152924 for
  further details. Thanks to Alex Tarkovsky <alextarkovsky@gmail.com> for the
  initial work.

  28 Nov 2006; Joshua Nichols <nichoj@gentoo.org> -mx4j-3.0.1.ebuild:
  Dropped earlier revision with equivalent keywords.

  28 Nov 2006; Joshua Nichols <nichoj@gentoo.org> mx4j-3.0.1-r1.ebuild:
  Stabilized on amd64 (see bug #155622).

  28 Nov 2006; Joshua Nichols <nichoj@gentoo.org>
  -files/mx4j-2.1.0-gentoo.patch, -mx4j-2.1.0.ebuild, -mx4j-2.1.0-r1.ebuild:
  Dropped old slot, which depends on an old version of resin.

  23 Nov 2006; Christian Faulhammer <opfer@gentoo.org> mx4j-3.0.1-r1.ebuild:
  stable x86, bug #155622

  28 Sep 2006; Vlastimil Babka <caster@gentoo.org> mx4j-3.0.1-r1.ebuild:
  Removed stray conditional jikes dep.

*mx4j-3.0.1-r1 (28 Sep 2006)

  28 Sep 2006; Joshua Nichols <nichoj@gentoo.org> +mx4j-3.0.1-r1.ebuild:
  Revision bump to support new Java system.

  03 Jul 2006; Joshua Nichols <nichoj@gentoo.org> +mx4j-3.0.1.ebuild:
  Version bump needed for tomcat-5.5.

  16 Dec 2005; Joshua Nichols <nichoj@gentoo.org> mx4j-2.1.0-r1.ebuild:
  Removed log4j dependency (bug #100275).

  30 Nov 2005; <nichoj@gentoo.org> mx4j-2.1.0-r1.ebuild:
  Added ~amd64 keyword (bug #110369).

*mx4j-2.1.0-r1 (24 Oct 2005)

  24 Oct 2005; Petteri Räty <betelgeuse@gentoo.org> +mx4j-2.1.0-r1.ebuild:
  New revision with fixed dependencies. Fixes bug #95830.

  19 May 2005; Jan Brinkmann <luckyduck@gentoo.org> mx4j-2.1.0.ebuild:
  stable on amd64 and x86

  16 Mar 2005; Jan Brinkmann <luckyduck@gentoo.org> mx4j-2.1.0.ebuild:
  mx4j now makes use of java-pkg_dosrc

*mx4j-2.1.0 (22 Jan 2005)

  22 Jan 2005; Jan Brinkmann <luckyduck@gentoo.org> +metadata.xml,
